# Aurora Core Rules

## Overview
Follow these rules for every change in the Aurora agentic frontend. The project mimics a modular IDE with Tauri-native capabilities—maintain separation of concerns and keep documentation synchronized.

## Technology Stack
- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite 7
- Zustand for state management
- TailwindCSS (custom dark palette) + limited global CSS
- Tauri 2 backend (Rust) for filesystem/shell persistence
- PNPM workspace

## Code Standards

### Pre-change Checklist
- Review `DOCS/01-ARCHITECTURE.md` and `DOCS/02-CODE-STYLE-PATTERNS.md` before touching code; align updates with the documented architecture.
- Confirm the change belongs in its own dedicated module or file to keep concerns separated.
- If the change alters flows, architecture, or conventions, update every relevant DOCS file in the same PR.

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`MainLayout`, `ChatPanel`).
- Hooks/stores: `use<Name>Store.ts`, `useThing.ts` (camelCase export).
- Services/utilities: kebab-case filenames (`llm-provider.ts`).
- Directories: kebab-case.
- Types/interfaces: live in `src/types`, PascalCase names.

### Code Structure
- Keep features split by domain folder (`components/chat`, `components/editor`, `services`, `store`, `tools`).
- Prefer colocated files per concern instead of monoliths—create new files when logic grows.
- Imports: external deps first, then absolute project paths, then relative siblings.
- Avoid large anonymous functions inside components—extract helpers/hooks.

### Essential Patterns
```tsx
// ✅ Compose panes with dedicated child components
export const MainLayout = () => (
  <PanelGroup>
    <Panel id="explorer"><FileExplorer /></Panel>
    <Panel id="editor"><EditorPanel /></Panel>
    {showChat && <Panel id="chat"><ChatPanel /></Panel>}
  </PanelGroup>
)
```

### Deprecated Patterns - DO NOT USE
```ts
// ❌ Dumping unrelated logic into one mega file
// ✅ Split into services, hooks, stores as needed
```

### Error Handling
- Wrap Tauri calls in try/catch; log via `console.error('[Module]', err)`.
- Return safe fallbacks (empty arrays, null) instead of throwing inside UI.

### Performance Guidelines
- Subscribe to Zustand slices to avoid rerender storms.
- Use refs for streaming data buffers (see `ChatPanel`).
- Keep heavy Tauri/file ops async and gated by `isTauri()`.

### Testing Requirements
- (Future) Use Vitest + RTL. Until tests exist, at least describe manual testing in PR notes.

### Documentation Standards
- Whenever architecture, conventions, or workflows change, update the corresponding `DOCS/*.md` files in the same PR.
- Reference files inline using @filepath where possible.

